"Hortensia," you say, handing the agent your stack of printed receipts, "can you see that these are checked?"

"Of course."

"Awful man." You shudder. "I don't see why they keep him around. If it were up me, I'd have him exiled."

Antony laughs. "I just wish he'd bathe. Who ever heard of a dirty holy man? Not how it's done at all. The funny thing is, when he came to the inaguration, he was perfectly hygenic. I think he does it on purpose."

"Sorry to interrupt," says Hortensia, "but we've verified that all of the receipts are genuine, as corroborated by the establishments in question. Of note is that he did linger at <strong>First Connection</strong>."

"Wonderful!" you cry, beaming. "As prompt as always."

"Just doing my job."

